	<div id="id10dc" class="post">
		<h2 class="title"><span class="image-wrapper"><img height="45" alt="Mom eats pho" width="226" class="title" src="../../../resources/net.databinder.components.RenderedLabel/3a3c4536"/><span class="title">Mom eats pho</span></span></h2>
		<div class="byline"><span>
			<span>By <span class="alias">Mom</span>, <span>on August 15, 2006</span></span>
			<span id="id10dd" class="tags">
					{&nbsp;<span><a href="../../../eat/tag/restaurants:%20pittsburgh/#selected-tag"><span>restaurants: pittsburgh</span></a></span>&nbsp;}
			</span>
		</span></div>
		<div><p>I don&#8217;t have a pho-to (heh-heh, a little foodie humor there!) because I forgot to take my camera with me, but we ate dinner at <a href="http://www.pittsburghlive.com/x/pittsburghtrib/s_318749.html">Tram&#8217;s Kitchen</a> tonight, and the pho there is the best I have had in Pittsburgh so far. The key ingredient to good pho is the broth, and theirs is rich and flavorful. <a href="http://www.billyprice.com">Poppy</a> always gets the large beef pho and I get the small one, along with a Vietnamese iced coffee. I love those.</p>


	<p>The only drawback to <strong>Tram&#8217;s</strong> is that the secret is out, and what used to be a great lunch destination no longer works for us because it has gotten so crowded that we can&#8217;t count on getting there, eating, and getting Bill back to the office in a reasonable amount of time. I was surprised that there were some empty tables at 6:00 PM tonight.</p></div>
	</div>
</div>

